      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/ac/model-form",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The constitutive model must capture the dominant physics of pedicle screw compression-bending: elastic-plastic material response of Ti-6Al-4V, frictional contact at screw-rod and rod-set-screw interfaces, and large-displacement geometric nonlinearity. Justification for omission of any physical phenomena (e.g. strain-rate effects, thermal effects) must be documented with supporting evidence."
      },
      "rationale": "The model employs a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model for Ti-6Al-4V (E = 114 GPa, σ_y = 880 MPa, E_t = 1.14 GPa) consistent with published tensile test data for ASTM F136 material. Geometric nonlinearity (NLGEOM ON) is activated to capture large-displacement bending. Frictional contact (μ = 0.2) is defined at all metal-metal interfaces. Strain-rate effects are omitted with justification: quasi-static loading at 5 mm/min produces strain rates < 10^-3 s^-1, well below the threshold for rate-dependent response in Ti-6Al-4V (documented in literature review DS-LR-2023-0012). Thermal effects omitted: ambient saline bath maintains isothermal conditions. Model form uncertainty contribution estimated at 1.2% of QoI via sensitivity analysis. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
