        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Test conditions must replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry, loading rate, and environmental conditions. Ideally, multiple loading rates or temperatures would be tested to assess condition sensitivity. At minimum, full traceability of load cell calibration (NIST-traceable, < 0.5% uncertainty) and displacement transducer calibration must be demonstrated."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was performed strictly per ASTM F1717-15 at a single loading condition (5 mm/min, 23 °C saline). Load cell calibration is NIST-traceable with < 0.3% uncertainty; displacement transducer calibration < 0.1% uncertainty. The single test condition represents the primary limitation of this validation activity: no variation in loading rate or temperature was explored, preventing assessment of condition sensitivity. This results in Gradation 2 (single well-characterized condition) against a required Gradation 3. The shortfall is addressed in the decision record via an offset rationale referencing the sensitivity analysis results and the narrow COU scope."
