      },
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison was performed using the ASME V&V 40 validation metric for all three QoIs. Results: (1) Construct stiffness: FEA 312 N/mm vs. exp. 308 N/mm, relative difference 1.3%, E/u_val = 0.74; (2) Yield force: FEA 1842 N vs. exp. 1878 N, relative difference 1.9%, E/u_val = 0.61; (3) Force at 40 mm: FEA 2310 N vs. exp. 2268 N, relative difference 1.9%, E/u_val = 0.45. All three QoIs satisfy both the < 10% relative difference and E/u_val < 1.96 acceptance criteria. Full force-displacement curves also compared graphically; FEA ensemble brackets experimental scatter throughout the loading range. Gradation 3 achieved."
