      },
      "rationale": "The three selected QoIs are precisely those specified in ASTM F1717-15 Section 9 and referenced in FDA guidance 'Testing of Orthopedic Implants' (May 2019) for 510(k) substantial equivalence demonstration. Construct stiffness characterizes the elastic load-sharing behavior relevant to clinical biomechanics; yield force defines the onset of permanent deformation relevant to implant integrity; force at 40 mm provides a post-yield performance metric. All three QoIs are directly observable in the validation experiment and directly predictable by the FEA model, ensuring a tight link between model output and decision-relevant performance. Gradation 3 achieved."
