      "rationale": "The validation activity is a direct replication of the COU: the same non-cannulated 7.5 × 45 mm pedicle screw design, the same ASTM F1717 fixture and loading protocol, and production-representative constructs from released manufacturing lots. The FEA model geometry was constructed from the same CAD files used for manufacturing. The regulatory context (Class II 510(k) compression-bending performance demonstration) is identical between validation and intended use. No scenario gaps were identified between the validation activity and the COU. The multi-laboratory design (two independent test facilities) strengthens confidence in the experimental reference data. Gradation 3 achieved."
